In Week 3, our team worked on cleaning and preparing a sample messy IT support dataset. 
Raw datasets often contain errors, missing values, duplicates, and inconsistent formats, which makes analysis difficult.
Therefore, data cleaning is an important step before performing data analysis.

Data Cleaning Process:

During the team work session, the following data cleaning steps were performed:
- Removing duplicate records
- Handling missing or null values
- Standardizing date and time formats
- Correcting inconsistent category names
- Verifying column data types

Team Collaboration:
The data cleaning activity was carried out as a team effort. Each team member analyzed different parts of the dataset and shared their observations. Team collaboration helped identify more data issues and provided deeper insights into the dataset.
Working together allowed us to clean the dataset more efficiently and understand the data patterns better.

Outcome:
After completing the cleaning process, the dataset was properly structured and ready for analysis in Power BI. 
The processed data will be used to create KPIs and dashboards to evaluate IT support team performance.
